frameDefinitions: An Entity has existed for a length of time, the Age.
Compared to its Competitors, a Standard is at the high end of a scale with respect to some Variable.

The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .

A Phenomenon is portrayed with respect to the Degree of likelihood that it will  be perceived and known, given the (usually implicit) Evidence, Perceiver, and the Circumstances in which it is considered.
A particular Binding_principle is (or is not) operative, that is, any obligations, restrictions, and any other aspects of the Binding_principle are (or are not) in effect.
frameExamples: This building is twenty thousand years <t>old</t>.
The taxpayer is supporting a system <t>unmatched</t> in wastefulness .
The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
It's abundantly <t>obvious</t> that we'll need to spend more time on public perception.
This law will only become in <t>effect</t> during the last three weeks of the year.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular age is under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is a function of the amount of time that the <fen>Entity</fen> has existed.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s age.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Age</fen> from the norm.
The Frame Element <fen>Expressor</fen> marks expressions that indicate a body part, gesture or other expression of the <fen>Entity</fen> that reflect its age.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is at a particular <fen>Age</fen>.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Variable</fen>.
The <fen>Variable</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Standard</fen> is located closest to one extreme in  comparison to its <fen>Competitors</fen>.
The role <fen>Competitors</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Standard</fen> with regard to the <fen>Variable</fen>.
The action that the agent undertakes to achieve the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the agent attempts to achieve by performing the <fen>Means</fen> action.
An entity directed by the agent as part of the <fen>Means</fen> action in order to accomplish the <fen>Goal</fen>.
A participant function of an <fen>Instrument</fen> or <fen>Means</fen> in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails
The place where <fen>Means</fen> action succeeds or fails.
An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.
The entity or facts that are undeniable given the <fen>Evidence</fen>.
The gradable aspect of a <fen>Phenomenon</fen> which concerns how likely it is that the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> be known. This frame element is incorporated by the lexical units in this frame.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Phenomenon</fen> in terms of how likely the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> would be known.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is obvious
The <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is the law, contract, principle, or other (set of) obligations that is (or is not) operational.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is in effect.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is or is not operational.
